# Part 2 — Phases 3–5

---

## Phase 3 — Dashboard & Reports (Weeks 6–7)

### Goal
Visual reporting layer. KPI cards, revenue/purchase/profit charts, and a dark-mode desktop dashboard. Zero data entry happens here — dashboard is read-only.

---

### Week 6 — Dashboard Overview + Sales

**Files created:**

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/app/(app)/app/dashboard/page.tsx` | Dashboard overview (server component fetches KPIs) |
| `src/app/(app)/app/dashboard/layout.tsx` | Dashboard layout — dark mode wrapper |
| `src/app/(app)/app/dashboard/sales/page.tsx` | Sales breakdown page |
| `src/components/dashboard/KPICard.tsx` | Single KPI metric card |
| `src/components/dashboard/KPIGrid.tsx` | 4-column (desktop) / 2×2 (mobile) KPI layout |
| `src/components/dashboard/RevenueChart.tsx` | Line chart — revenue over time |
| `src/components/dashboard/SalesBreakdownChart.tsx` | Donut chart — sales by category |
| `src/components/dashboard/TopProductsTable.tsx` | TanStack Table — top selling products |
| `src/components/dashboard/DateRangeFilter.tsx` | Date range picker (7d / 30d / 90d / custom) |
| `src/components/dashboard/DashboardHeader.tsx` | Title + date filter + export button |
| `src/components/dashboard/InsightsSummaryCard.tsx` | Purple gradient card: unread insights CTA |
| `src/app/api/dashboard/overview/route.ts` | GET: KPIs (total revenue, total purchases, profit margin, low stock count) |
| `src/app/api/dashboard/sales/route.ts` | GET: sales data grouped by period |
| `src/lib/queries/dashboard.ts` | SQL query builders for dashboard aggregations |

**KPI calculations** (all server-side, scoped by `business_id` + date range):

| KPI | Query |
|-----|-------|
| Total Revenue | `SUM(total_amount) FROM transactions WHERE type='sale' AND status='confirmed'` |
| Total Purchases | `SUM(total_amount) FROM transactions WHERE type='purchase' AND status='confirmed'` |
| Gross Profit | Revenue − Cost of Goods Sold (sum of `cost_price * quantity` for sold items) |
| Low Stock Items | `COUNT(*) FROM stock_levels sl JOIN product_variants pv ON sl.variant_id=pv.id WHERE sl.quantity <= pv.reorder_threshold` |

**Dark mode strategy**: The dashboard layout wraps children in a `<div className="dark">` container. All dashboard components use `dark:` Tailwind variants. The Tailwind config has `darkMode: 'class'`. Only the dashboard uses dark mode — all other app pages remain light.

