**Role enforcement** — every API route checks role:

```typescript
// src/lib/auth/checkRole.ts
export async function checkRole(
  supabase: SupabaseClient,
  businessId: string,
  requiredRoles: ('owner' | 'manager' | 'staff')[]
) {
  const { data: member } = await supabase
    .from('business_members')
    .select('role')
    .eq('business_id', businessId)
    .eq('user_id', (await supabase.auth.getUser()).data.user?.id)
    .single();

  if (!member || !requiredRoles.includes(member.role)) {
    return { authorized: false, role: member?.role };
  }
  return { authorized: true, role: member.role };
}
```

| Action | Owner | Manager | Staff |
|--------|-------|---------|-------|
| Log transaction (chat) | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
| View products/inventory | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
| Create/edit products | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ |
| Delete anything | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| View dashboard (all) | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ |
| View financials (profit) | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| Manage team | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| Edit business settings | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ |
| View own transactions | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |

Frontend enforcement: a `<RoleGate>` component wraps UI elements. Checks role from `useAuthStore` and renders children only if authorized. Unauthorized routes redirect to `/app/chat`.

```tsx
// src/components/auth/RoleGate.tsx
export function RoleGate({ allowed, children, fallback }: {
  allowed: ('owner' | 'manager' | 'staff')[];
  children: React.ReactNode;
  fallback?: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  const role = useAuthStore(s => s.role);
  if (!allowed.includes(role)) return fallback ?? null;
  return <>{children}</>;
}
```

